Set up a headless WordPress instance using Docker Compose.

Initialize containers
docker-compose up -d

Install WP, install & activate some useful plugins, install & activate no-theme which displays nothing.
docker-compose run --rm wp-cli install-wp

If you want to run wp-cli commands:
docker-compose run --rm wp-cli plugin list

If you want to access mysql:
mysql -uwordpress -pwordpress -h127.0.0.1 -P8306 wordpress

WordPress REST API is available at:
http://localhost:8080/wp-json/
